# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# TaskFlow — Frontend Environment Variables
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Copy this file to frontend/.env and fill in your real values.
# NEVER commit .env with real secrets to git.
# Vite ONLY exposes variables prefixed with VITE_
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ─── API URL ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# In development, leave empty — Vite dev proxy forwards /api to localhost:8000
# In production, set to your backend URL:
# VITE_API_URL=https://taskflow-api.onrender.com/api
VITE_API_URL=

# ─── Google OAuth ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com

# ─── GitHub OAuth ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VITE_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=your-github-client-id
